properties.sfomuseum:creditline: Transfer from City and County of San Francisco
properties.sfomuseum:description: Collection of newsprint clippings containing airport resolutions:a. Bill No. 7914, Ordinance No. 7428 (New Series), “Authorizing and directing the mayor and clerk of the Board of Supervisors to execute a lease in behalf of the City and County of San Francisco with the Mills Estate Incorporated, for certain lands situated in the County of San Mateo, State of California, required for air port purposes,” approved March 11, 1927;b. Resolution No. 27075 (New Series), “Upon recommendation of the city engineer, be it resolved that the mayor and the clerk of the Board of Supervisors are hereby authorized and directed to execute in behalf of the City and County of San Francisco [...] the right to construct, maintain and operate a three-inch (3”) water pipe beneath the Market Street Railway Company’s right of way [...]”;c. Resolution No. 27056 (New Series), “Upon recommendation of the city engineer, be it resolved that the mayor and the clerk of the Board of Supervisors are hereby authorized and directed to execute, in behalf of the City and County of San Francisco [...] the right to construct, maintain and operate a three-inch (3”) water pipe beneath the Southern Pacific Company’s right of way [...].”
